-- Japan, Tanzania to Jointly Explore, Develop Minerals Including Rare Earth
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-12-07T05:16:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/japan-tanzania-to-jointly-explore-develop-minerals-including-rare-earth.html
Japan and Tanzania agreed to jointly
explore and develop minerals in the African nation. Tanzania is
likely to have rare earth and rare metal deposits, the state-
owned Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corp. said in a
statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
